    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup for April 20th centers around a clear marquee play: **Gunnar Henderson**. With a robust score of 83.29, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from an optimal leadoff spot and a wind-aided environment that bolsters his power-speed profile. While his aggressive base-stealing potential is slightly tempered by the matchup, he remains the engine of our 5x5 production today. Joining him in the \"Strong\" category is **Andy Pages**, who draws the most favorable matchup of the slate against Quintana. The combination of a 5.04 xERA and a generous +14% park factor makes **Andy Pages** an elite value play at an OF slot, significantly outperforming his baseline expectations.\n\nThe decision-making process at the UTIL and MI spots required careful calibration against the pitching opposition. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (57.76) and **Jacob Wilson** (60.20) are slated to start, but the former faces a daunting task against Detmers; **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**\u2019s score is kept afloat primarily by his elite xwOBA, yet he remains at risk if the lefty suppresses his contact quality. **Nolan Schanuel** serves as our most notable bench candidate at 50.08. Despite a decent matchup, **Nolan Schanuel** was relegated to the bench because his overall efficiency metrics trail the combination of **Brady House**\u2014who benefits from a favorable platoon advantage against Elder\u2014and the high-upside start of **Dominic Smith**, whose platoon edge against Irvin outweighs the marginal utility of keeping **Nolan Schanuel** active. We are continuing to monitor **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Jackson Merrill**, who are unavailable today, forcing us to lean heavily on depth pieces like **Liam Hicks** and **Nasim Nunez** to maintain our competitive edge in the scarcity-driven stolen base category.",
